                    <div class="plash-breast">
                        <div class="breast-title">What is a Tummy Tuck (Abdominoplasty)?</div>
                        <div class="breast-text">
                            <p>After childbirth, weight loss or weight gain, and with age, the abdomen becomes stretched
                                out and loses its youthful form. So many women say that no matter what they do at the
                                gym, the excess skin and fat in their lower abdomen simply won’t go away. A Tummy Tuck
                                or abdominoplasty is a surgical procedure that removes this excess skin. Additionally,
                                during the procedure, your TOPS plastic surgeon will bring the abdominal muscles that
                                were separated by pregnancy or weight gain (a condition called rectus diastasis) back
                                together to help bring back your hourglass figure. These specialized suture techniques
                                serve as an internal corset to help cinch in your waist and define your curves. In most
                                cases, liposuction of the abdomen and love handles is performed to accentuate your waist
                                and maximize your results. This liposculpting technique, as well as internal sculpting
                                sutures, help to really define your abdomen, creating a sculpted, sexy look. The TOPS
                                plastic surgeons then resculpt your belly button through a new hole in the skin after
                                the skin from the top of your abdomen is pulled down.</p>
                            <p>On some occasions, the TOPS plastic surgeons can perform what is called a mini Tummy
                                Tuck. This is reserved for women or men who have very limited excess skin and only
                                require a small amount of skin removal and limited tightening of the abdominal muscles.
                                Women who are typically the best candidates for mini Tummy Tuck have only a small pooch
                                overlying their c-section scar.</p>
                        </div>
